05:10.840 --> 05:12.432
I have no idea.

05:12.480 --> 05:14.573
Hence my use of
the word "mysterious."

05:14.610 --> 05:16.771
Apparently Gregson
recommended my services,

05:16.810 --> 05:18.744
and, uh, they won't
tell me anything else

05:18.780 --> 05:21.419
until I've signed
a confidentiality agreement.

05:21.450 --> 05:23.111
Uh, is that what
you're going to wear?

05:23.150 --> 05:25.345
What's wrong with it?

05:25.390 --> 05:27.881
It... I'm pretty sure you slept
in that T-shirt last night,

05:27.920 --> 05:31.378
and, um, the guys on Wall
Street are a little more...

05:31.430 --> 05:32.920
formal in the way they dress.

05:32.960 --> 05:34.518
Those are costumes.

05:34.560 --> 05:36.699
I loathe bankers.

05:36.730 --> 05:38.391
They rigged the roulette wheel
of commerce,

05:38.430 --> 05:39.829
very nearly destroyed
the world economy,

05:39.870 --> 05:42.134
and they still think
if they wear suits

05:42.170 --> 05:43.535
they'll be treated
like respectable folk

05:43.570 --> 05:45.902
instead of the crooks
that they are.

05:47.110 --> 05:49.544
My name is Jim Fowkes.

05:49.580 --> 05:50.979
I'm the chief investment
officer.

05:51.010 --> 05:53.570
This is Daniel Cho,
our chief financial officer,

05:53.620 --> 05:54.917
another in-house
board member...

05:54.950 --> 05:56.440
Yep, you're all
chief of something.

05:56.490 --> 05:57.843
What do you want?

05:57.890 --> 05:59.687
Mm.

05:59.720 --> 06:02.848
FOWKES:
This is our COO, Peter Talbott.

06:02.890 --> 06:05.450
Every quarter, he fields
a conference call with

06:05.490 --> 06:07.128
our institutional investors.

06:07.160 --> 06:09.993
These people control
huge pension funds.

06:10.030 --> 06:12.533
As far as they're
concerned, Peter's the
voice of the company.

06:12.570 --> 06:14.788
This quarter's call was
supposed to happen yesterday.

06:14.840 --> 06:17.764
We had to reschedule,
because Peter didn't show up.

06:17.810 --> 06:19.630
Nobody has any idea
where he is.

06:19.680 --> 06:21.636
And if you don't get this
call back on the books soon,

06:21.680 --> 06:23.545
people will start to whisper.

06:23.580 --> 06:26.549
When these people whisper,
Mr. Holmes,

06:26.580 --> 06:27.808
millions of dollars disappear.

06:27.850 --> 06:30.080
The gentleman
we spoke to,

06:30.120 --> 06:31.610
a, uh, Captain Gregson,

06:31.650 --> 06:33.049
he said that the NYPD
couldn't get involved

06:33.090 --> 06:35.081
until Peter had been
missing for two days.

06:35.120 --> 06:36.758
He also said that

06:36.790 --> 06:38.883
you were the finest
investigator he'd ever known.

06:38.930 --> 06:42.559
We'd like to hire you
and your, uh... associate.

06:42.600 --> 06:43.692
Bodyguard.

06:43.730 --> 06:45.960
